# Analysis of Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The target structure consists of two separate constructions:

1. **Left Structure:**
   - 4 blocks total: 1 blue cube, 3 orange triangular prisms, and 1 green rectangular block
   - 3 layers: orange triangular prisms at bottom, blue cube in middle, green rectangular block on top

2. **Right Structure:**
   - 9 blocks total: 4 orange cylindrical blocks at bottom, 2 yellow rectangular blocks in middle, 1 green cube and 1 blue cube stacked above, with 1 yellow half-cylinder on top
   - 4 layers: orange cylinders, yellow rectangles, green and blue cubes, yellow half-cylinder

## Spatial Relationships

**Left Structure:**
- Base: Three orange triangular prisms (two on sides and one in middle)
- Middle: One blue cube positioned on the left side
- Top: One green rectangular block placed horizontally across the top

**Right Structure:**
- Base: Four orange cylindrical pillars arranged in a square formation
- Second layer: Two yellow rectangular blocks placed horizontally across the pillars
- Third layer: One green cube at bottom with one blue cube stacked on top
- Fourth layer: One yellow half-cylinder dome on top of the blue cube

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

## Left Structure:
- Blue cube (index 1) - 1 unit
- Green rectangular block (index 4) - 1 unit
- Orange triangular prisms (indices 13, 14, 15) - 3 units

## Right Structure:
- Orange cylindrical blocks (index 8) - 4 units
- Yellow rectangular blocks (indices 5, 7) - 2 units
- Green cube (index 2) - 1 unit
- Blue cube (index 1) - 1 unit
- Yellow half-cylinder dome (index 9) - 1 unit
